"n.混合物 【英】 n.混合物(a combination or mixture; blend) 【记】 联想记忆： am-alg-am，前后两者 am结合→混合 n. 混合物 = blend; 汞合金 【记】前后两个am结合－混合 【记】a male game 男性的体育比赛需要各个成员合在一起成为团队 amalgam (n.)  c.1400, ""blend of mercury with another metal; soft mass formed by chemical manipulation,"" from Old French amalgame or directly from Medieval Latin amalgama, ""alloy of mercury (especially with gold or silver),"" an alchemists' word, perhaps an alteration of Latin malagma ""poultice, plaster,"" probably from Arabic al-malgham ""an emollient poultice or unguent for sores (especially warm)"" [Francis Johnson, ""A Dictionary of Persian, Arabic, and English""], perhaps from Greek malagma ""softening substance,"" from malassein ""to soften,"" from malakos ""soft."""
